caption: The food is always well prepared and yummy, cashiers hands over great service. I love how neat it is and ambience. Will come visit again.
We had a wonderful  in this spot. We loved the first-rate environment and the meals. The waiters are super attentive. I’m content we eventually decided to try this place.
I tried this place before with a friend and I am hooked since then. I loved the fantastic character and fresh food and drinks. Highly recommended.
I simply enjoy their food. I always get excellent service there. The place is always clean and the workers are always very friendly. Would recommend to others.
intimate, speakeasy-date spot.

I’m a local and don’t give five stars lightly as there are many incredible restaurants in this neighborhood - even this block - but this place is awesome. Cool vibes and great cocktails (I recommend the pineapple Negroni). Karagi fried chicken is the best I’ve had anywhere in NY. Avoid the ribeye but everything else is fantastic. My favorite hidden gem on the menu is the sweet potato. Mandatory every time!
Karasu has great food, great service, great drinks, and a great atmosphere. They have flavorful and delicious small plates. Great for a date night or with friends!

First off, the food was delicious. We had the ribeye for two, which was as excellent as the articles say, and the yaki imo, and the mushrooms, all delicious. They were very cautious with my allergy, swapping out sauces and things where there might have been an issue. Our server was wonderful, and was very helpful with suggestions for drinks and what appetizers to get. My one issue, which is not a problem with the place itself, but with my expectations going in after reading the reviews in New York magazine and other publications, was that it was described as having a low-key and quiet vibe. It was definitely chill-- go in a t-shirt and jeans if you want and you won't feel out of place-- but I guess in the years since those reviews were written, things have changed, so that at least on a Saturday night it was absolutely not quiet. The music was great, and I had a really enjoyable meal there, but know that if you want to have a quiet evening date, this isn't going to be that.
4 stars because the portions are small and the prices are exuberant for the area. However, the flavors are big, the drinks are delicious and the service is grand.

The vibes are good.  The food was good, but not great and way overpriced for the laughably small portions of salmon/fish. The service left a lot to be desired.  Tl;dr: overpriced for a neighborhood spot and food not worth the visit from outside the area.
Two time winner. Fantastic service that’s knowledgeable and friendly. The ribeye for two is as good as everyone says. And the other dishes shine too.
Very good. The grilled fish was yummy.
Fresh salmon rice bowl and duck soba noodles!

This is a really nice izakaya spot tucked away behind a door in Walters. The menu has all the right items that will fit varied tastes. I had the soba which was fantastic. They also have a really good sake and Japanese whiskey selection.
Favorite secret spot. Fried chicken 💯🍗
Karasu pretty much the bomb

Great lil "speak-easy" bar and restaurant at the back of Walter's. A small menu selection that hits all the right notes. The shitake mushroom pudding and miso clams are a must order. The cocktails were a lil confusing with the crushed ice and pineapple that made more of a snow cone in Hawii. The portions are small and will require several dishes to be comfortable in the belly. Price point is quite high for a small portion of duck soba (delicious but tiny when for me).
Great drinks and delicious food...cocktails were very nice.
This place never fails to impress. They serve excellent dishes for affordable pricing, there is no waiting time even when they are loaded.

I visited Karasu about 6 months ago and am still thinking about the experience. Right when I walked into Karasu, I was confronted with unfriendly wait staff; no one smiled and because I was slightly early for a reservation we were asked to leave. It felt stuffy, like they were unconcerned with whether I chose to stay or go. The food was fine - nothing really blew me away like I was expecting for a place so highly rated.

Been wanting to go here for a while and it did not disappoint. It's a cute little restaurant in the back of Walter's (just walk straight back through Walter's). Moody, dimly lit, romantic for a date, also good for small get togethers with friends. Definitely need a reservation and not the type of place you're going to get a drink and stand. Food:  Fried chicken and Tonkatsu were fabulous. The somen noodles were fine - good, but just fine, probably something to skip. Drinks: we had 4 of the cocktails and they were all really good. The descriptions sound like they wouldn't go together, but it was they were all surprisingly delicious. Definitely will be back.

Our second time coming here, this time with another couple so that we could order more food from the unique offerings on the menu. The steak is cooked to perfection, charred just enough on the outside and perfectly pink in the middle with just enough fat to add flavor without being too chewy. The trout dish we had was delicious and light. Of course, the Karaage fried chicken was excellent, as was the Water Spinach and whatever sauce it came served with. Great meal and the price wasn't terribly high considering the amount of food we had.

It's one of these places that get everything right. The mysterious backdoor, the small but airy space, the dim lights, the professional staff - just relax, everything has been designed to maximize your experience. Japanese bar food, such as fried chicken wings, duck soba, pickled vegetables: perfect. Sophisticated cocktails where shiso leaves bath in gin, plum wine blends with tequila, and miso dissolves in shochu: another round please. We also enjoyed their limited but well-curated sake menu. Kanpai!
Amazing

Helpful, courteous, and professional staff. Alejandro the manager especially is attentive. However the portions are rather stingy. Has plenty of $20 plus meal choices that you could eat in one large bite. The atmosphere is good, but not unique for upscale Japanese.
Cute spot behind Walter's in Fort Greene. Enjoyed the trout but found the soba was a bit too salty for me.
I had the tonkatsu, and a sister midnight. I loved all of it.

Amazing Japanese. Salmon was amazing. Bartender pleased me not a big sake fan taste with Yamahai! I regret we couldn't fit more  space is small but nice decorated, awesome mirrorjob and lamp. Dont let yourself being sited in deadend of a bar, straight away we jave asked for replacement, otherwise we could have left (not positive spot). Boneless chicken amazing. Go to place gor small date, as the place is tiny. Happy experience overall ♡♡♡
Very interesting and cute Japanese restaurant with speak easy vibe hidden inside another restaurant with no Vibe.
Drinks: four stars. Food: three stars.
Great Japanese Whisky and one of the best steaks in the city.

Pleasantly surprised.   No sushi.  Low key.  Great food.   Odd that the raw menu that had “grilled” shrimp on it.  When I asked the server how grilled shrimp could be on the Raw menu she said “ it’s lightly grilled “.  Ended up being some of the most over cooked, tough rubbery shrimp I’ve ever had.    Too much attention in the beginning ( early reservation ) turned into perhaps not enough service clearing plates and getting our check.   Other than that, a complete class evening with great food.

Really great snacks! One of the best I ever tried, specially the boneless chicken! And the best hostess ever! She found a way for us to eat even without reservation she helps us choose the food and the drinks with the best hostess spirit!
Be sure to choose either dining at the bar or table.

Food and atmosphere are excellent! Definitely a go to spot. The service is exceptional and the bartenders are worth it for the cocktails alone. Fantastic cocktails list but don't be afraid to go off menu.... especially with Chris. The food has never let me down and the steak is truly one of the best steaks I've ever eaten. Prices aren't cheap but also not unreasonable. Never had a bad time here!
Went back for our anniversary and chose to sit at the bar because our previous experience had been so good. Tonight was not as good as previous nights.
Great drinks and cool vibe. -1 star because of the bartenders attitude. Other than that, excellent time!

The door is at the end of Walters. It can’t be hard to find. Once you’re in is a intimate space. Excellent selection of drinks. Very good sakes. The food is what I think makes these speakeasy unique. It’s incredible.
Great drinks and small plates.
Come for the happy hour tonkatsu sandwich. YUM!
Great ambiance and drinks. The food wasn’t anything extraordinary. Very expensive tonkatsu.

Went here twice.  1st time bartender made good drinks but the hostess that works at the door was quite rude and unaccomodating.  2nd time I went, same rude hostess and drinks and service were subpar.  The atmosphere is nice and I cant speak to the food quality.
Rushed to leave with hovering wait staff which was the only thing that lessened the otherwise wonderful experience
good food and excellent cocktails. Vegetarian options are hit-or-miss, though. Terrific pickles, and a delightful rich yam dish. But their veggie ramen is really bland.

Really fun place with expert cocktails and outstanding small and shareable plates. Japanese pickles are a great palate cleanser to start. Highly recommend the fried chicken thighs or the tonkatsu pork but maybe not both unless you have a larger party to share.

Overrated. Everything was mostly good but not great. Don’t get the potato dish.. I thought it would be more than just a potato but it was just a potato. There are some well crafted Japanese architectural elements that contribute to a nice ambiance.

This place is beautifully designed, the presentation and services were fantastic. We really enjoyed our cocktails but were left pretty underwhelmed by the dishes we ordered. The Karage stood out from the field as being beautifully breaded and fried but the seafood portion of the menu that we tried, the crab salad, sashimi and tuna collar were all somewhat spiceless.
(Translated by Google) Bessssssssssssst.  (Original) Besssssssssssst.

I had trouble finding the door to get in and ended up in the hallway to a private residence  and then the restaurant’s kitchen... but that’s part of the appeal I guess. The atmosphere and staff were good. The happy hour cocktail was great. The portions are small so ordering a lot is needed (and thus pricey). Everything was delicious tho and some of the dishes were rather unique.
Love everything about this place.
Just take my word for it and get the steak for two, even if you're by yourself.
Love the ambiance and hidden factor. The happy hour menu was great (except the sake, which was subpar). Food was pretty good and service was great.

Super delicious dinner and cocktails. The karaage is a year-round must have and the menu changes seasonally. Today we had the yaki imo Japanese roasted sweet potato which was super super amazing. We also had the karaage, green salad and crab salad. The ambiance is super cute, a little dim because it's a bar, and Brooklyn sexy. Highly recommend!! 😊😊😊
Cool hidden spot that is not too pretentious, if you are near by you should stop by!

It's funny because the concept and ambience is appreciable however the bartender could be a little more enthusiastic. Overall food and cocktails were ok. Nice to have in the area but if you go to Manhattan or Williamsburg regularly, not really special enough to go out of your way. Walters is pretty great though.
Loved their steaks!
Love it apps

Very cool speakeasy. In the back of Walter’s Restaurant and set up as a speakeasy which is very cool. Good selection of Japanese whiskies as well as decent shochu and sake. A bit pricey but good atmosphere.

Good speakeasy with surprisngly great food.  Intimate setting and ambience, great place to get a drink with a friend or date.  Pickles are also very good.  Prime rib is huge, and cooked in a Japanese sauce. fish has great flavors.  Highly recommend for drinks and food.
Noodles were so delicious. I think it's made in-house. I hope it's made in-house.
Hidden behind the western restaurant its an oriental fusion with good food and cocktails.

The food is phenomenal! Everything tasted great, especially the grilled squid and tonkatsu. However, the portion sizes can be misleading, this is not a tapas place. I would suggest each guest get an appetizer and main dish, rather than sharing a bunch of plates.
Good

Awesome selection for date night (seriously, keep it small the space is tiny) and be ready to shell out the cash. The food and cocktail menu are incredible, but do not expect a traditional Japanese meal. They play with all kinds of flavors; the udon with lamb and mint is a great example and a great selection. The fried chicken and sashimi platter were also tasty. Definitely make a reservation.

A truly fantastic meal and a fantastic experience. And seriously, if you come here and don't try the fried chicken, you're missing something truly special. Is it chicken tempura? That was our guess but who knows?  Whatever. Try this.
Excellent drinks and ambiance. Food is a bit pricey but still a good option for a place for dinner and drinks. Best to have a reservation, waits for a table can be long on the weekend.
This place is 💯 Dig the secret entrance, the Mighty Mighty cocktail is excellent, all the food is delicious, the aesthetic is awesome
Possibly the best place in the neighborhood for dinner/drinks/ambiance. The sashimi is always good and cocktails are excellent.

Get the steak! We went on a Friday night and swooned over the fried chicken, the pickles, and the steak. The cocktails and happy hour treats were also worth ordering. There are few Brooklyn dinners better than eating Japanese steak with ponzu in a restaurant behind a restaurant (Walter’s), with Ethiopian jazz playing and great drinks.

If you're looking for a great date place or a place to be totally incognito, this is it! Small Japanese speakeasy located behind one of my local favorites, Walter's. Sublime cocktails and nice small bites. The large plate menu is limited but well done. They also have a reasonable happy hour till 7. Usually a couple of drink special and 2 light snacks.
Great food, great cocktails, good service. Solid every time. It's a pricy spot though so just enjoy it ok?

The food is nice but a little bit pricey. The phenomenon is good for a laid back dinner. It's better to make a reservation but you have to go. They are not friendly with the cancellation and will charge extra fee.
Best TONKATSU and cocktails in the city!!! Truly amazing!!!

Hidden Japanese cocktail bar in the back of the Walter's Fort Greene. Large selection of Japanese whiskeys, sake, and shochu. Get yourself a highball with the housemade apple soda. Raw bar and restaurant as well.

Small "izakaya" behind Walter's. The food was good, but very limited selection. And there aren't any sushi, rolls, and other usual things that would be on the menu at an izakaya. And even when my friends and I dropped a lot of $$$ that night, the server was eh... Not sure if I'll be back.
You're mostly paying for the ambience here. Food is mediocre, at best. Overpriced, bland, and incredibly inauthentic. Very disappointed.
Cool, but pricey as hell. Grumpy bartenders.

Excellent, warm and welcoming service. Small menu of small plates with unique flavors. Extensive drink menu. A little onyx jewelbox of a room with a pretty bar. A romantic spot and the hidden vibe makes it that much more special.
How to get in: Head to the back of Walter’s and through the unmarked door. Reservations are accepted on Karasu’s website.
Sophisticated cocktails & small plates, well-designed and lit
Great find, cozy atmosphere, original take on the food, with very subtle flavors (at first it feels a bit bland)

I'm entranced. After dinner at Walter's, a couple friends and I headed to the back of the Fort Greene, Brooklyn restaurant and entered into this mysterious, completely black, no signage door that led to one of the greatest speakeasy type bars I've ever come across.  There isn't a ton of space as far as tables go (maybe 8?) but there's also a bar area and, if you're lucky, you can snag a seat there without having to make a reservation. I was automatically impressed with the service from the moment I sat down - attentive bartenders and they were knowledgeable and willing to explain drinks if needed. My friends and I tried out a few different options and each of us loved all of the ones we tried.  If you're a gin drinker, the Bee Side (gin, basil, lemon, lychee) is amazing.  For darker rum drinkers, the Nettai is good (and strong) but it's essentially shaved ice like... definitely unexpected. But, for so much ice, it's actually strong (seriously) and there's quite a lot of drink in it.  Both of my friends had the Wave (gin, coconut, lime, etc.) and really liked it. I'm not a coconut fan, but they both are and enjoyed it.  An odd thing about his place is that, as my friend said it, "it's sort of Russian roulette with the glass your drink is served in." One friend ordered a drink and it was in a small cocktail glass, then a bartender made the same exact drink 10 minutes later for someone else in a glass two inches taller than her. Slightly odd, but I think that's just the way it is... the luck of the draw. However, all cocktails are $14, no matter what sized glass you get.  The ambiance, experience and true chemistry that goes into making these drinks is unmatched. I'm excited to go back and actually have dinner here next time!
Pretentious, marginal food
Wonderful experience.
This place is awesome! The cocktails are creative, delicious, and strong. Highly recommend the karaage, Caesar salad, and rib eye for two.
Excellent cocktails, unique appetizers and classic main dishes. Absolutely amazing food.
Great food and great drinks.  With an atmosphere to match.
Awesome decor, interesting drinks and menu, service can be on the slow side thougb

We needed a balanced cocktail after a 'long' week and before dinner at Samui (highly recommend) and I had a hankering for the Thrice Rice. This time the experience was much better with the new bartender because he seemed more personable or engaging. It's a relaxing speak-easy type place until it gets crowded and it becomes difficult to enjoy your drink or appreciate the design of the space.

I was so pleased when I found out this 'secret' space opened up at the back of Walter's. It's a small, but stunning space, with Japanese mid-century modern decor, complementing the beautifully executed cocktails and cuisine.
Great drinks and ambience! Accompanied by tasty Japanese food as well. Coming by early when it opens will be a better bet to get a table.
Nice date spot for low key Japanese vibes. Bit of a wait to be seated but to be expected on a Friday night. Good selection of Japanese whiskeys. Hostess was very communicative and friendly.

the cocktails are excellent and are served in ornamental glassware that reminded me of some of my favorite bars in Japan. the selection of Japanese whiskeys was decent. if you wanted to drink sake, this isn't the place you would go.  what was disappointing was the food. the karaage was par with the fried chicken you would get at any basic Japanese izakaya: tasty but commonplace. the broccoli rabe had little flavor and the udon we received was staggeringly bland.  the space, the drinks, the vibe—a lot is going right for karasu and I'd try it again. but i hope they start putting more effort in in the kitchen

Karasu is this amazing speakeasy located inside Walter's. Come in straight to the door besides Walter's restrooms and you'll be welcomed in this tiny Japanese hideout. Their Cocktails are flavorful and the Koji Ribeye was charred to perfection; not to mention their selection is reasonably priced. One of the lesser known Speakeasies, but definitely worth your trip!
Gorgeous interior. Food is good, and interestingly different if you're only used to edamame and sushi when it comes to Japanese. Plus it's always fun to eat in a hidden secret izakaya.
Exciting, intimate, fantastic place. Can't wait to go back.
Service and food was excellent. Drinks were super tasty.
Delicious food and wonderful hospitality. Some of the best steak and uni pasta I have ever had. It's a must when visiting brooklyn.
Amazing cocktails, food, and terrific service and ambiance
Shani's fav
Amazing but please don't tell anyone from Manhattan bc then I won't be able to get a table :)
